Untitled Document
 Spending on Rich Internet Applications is going to exceed $500M by 2011 !
“It's really time for US enterprises to start switching to the Web as a platform for application delivery. They have stayed in the client-server world for too long, compared to the rapid adoption of Web 2.0 in the consumer space. The easiest way for stepping up to Web 2.0 (Web as a platform) is through the door called RIA.”
								  - BERT HALSTEAD
								  Chief Architect, Curl
For today's (and tomorrow's) applications that run via the Web, should they be AJAX-based - or do AIR/Flash/Flex, JavaFX, or Silverlight offer better results? And what about Appcelerator, OpenLaszlo, or Curl, or any of the other many open source alternatives that have emerged? 
To inspire you to come to AJAXWorld 2008 East and choose your direction for Rich Internet Applications, we bring you here the entire Conference Program, from which you can see that there are sessions covering just about ever RIA technology currently available, whether your interest is AIR 1.0, Flex 2 and 3, Curl 5.0, Open Laszlo 4.0, Silverlight 2.0, Rico 2.0, Zend Framework 1.5, Grails 1.0, Groovy 1.5 - you name it, we have speakers who are knowledgeable about it and giving a session or part of a session about it.
 
Come see why, as a recent ZapThink report predicted,  spending on RIAs is going to exceed $500 million dollars by 2011. No company developing web applications can afford to wait any longer to solidify their Rich Internet Application strategy: 2008 is the Decision Year for RIAs.
				
2008 is the year that US enterprises are switching in increasing numbers to the Web as a platform for application delivery, and 2008 too will for many enterprises be the Decision Year for their choice of RIA platform. Make that choice in New York City in March! AJAXWorld Conference & Expo is the place to be if you want easy access under one roof to a welter of resources, ideas and examples to help you decide.
The extensive Expo floor additionally will allow you to follow up on the premier solutions already available and to choose which best suits your needs. In short, AJAXWorld is where you can discover everything you're going to need for business survival and Web success in 2008. 								
								
Hope to see you in New York City at the 6th International AJAXWorld !
Jeremy Geelan
Conference Chair, AJAXWorld 2008 
http://ajaxworld.com

AJAX Security Bootcamp
Introducing the world's first-ever full, one-day immersive "AJAX Security Bootcamp" - led by one of the world's foremost AJAX security experts and teachers, Billy Hoffman. 
			                                
			                                To be held for the first time on March 18, 2008 at the historic Roosevelt Hotel, AJAX Security Bootcamp is a compelling, intensive, one-day, hands-on training program that will teach Web developers, Web designers, and other Web professionals how to build secure AJAX applications and demonstrate what the best practices are to mitigate security problems in AJAX applications.
ALL-NEW iPhone Developer Summit 2008 East in NYC (March 19-20, 2008)
After the resounding success of the first-ever iPhone technical sessions at AJAXWorld on the West coast in September '07, SYS-CON Events has great pride in announcing that the world's first-ever 100% dedicated 2-day iPhone Developer Summit will be an integral part of the AJAXWorld Conference & Expo 2008 East in New York City (19-20 March, 2008).
The groundbreaking iPhone Developer Summit is chaired by iPhone Developer's Journal editor-in-chief Kevin Hoffman.
Sessions include:
Day 1 (March 19)
Day 2 (March 20)

Top Ten Reasons To Attend AJAXWorld :
Attendance will improve your company's ability to adapt and prosper in the age of Rich Internet Application and the rich-web, user-centric environment. 
Attending delegates will leave AJAXWorld 2008 East with resources, ideas and examples they can apply immediately. 
Delegates have a wide choice of technical sessions on not only AJAX but also leading alternatives for creating rich-web functionalities and applications. 
Many fast-expanding alternatives now exist: find out what they all are and get expert advice on choosing between them. 
As an optional pre-conference extra, there's a special one-day "AJAX Security Bootcamp" on March 18 led by leading security expert Billy Hoffman: a worldwide first! 
Whether we really need JavaScript 2.0 is just one of the issues that will be vigorously discussed: there are no holy cows at AJAXWorld, only business and technology realities. 
AJAXWorld is the only event in the world to co-locate a full 2-day "iPhone Developer Summit" for anyone considering handheld portable devices as a target application platform. 
The founders, CTOs, and leading lights of many of the RIA world's leading pioneers will be giving technical sessions and participating in our unique SYS-CON.TV Power Panels.
All Golden Pass Delegates receive a video archive of all sessions on DVD, so that you can eventually catch up even on sessions you weren't able to attend in person. 
More than 10,000 developers, architects, IT managers, analysts, VCs, and C-Level executives have already attended AJAXWorld.
